            <p class="list">* What else you should know about your online privacy</p>
            <p>What personally identifiable information is collected from you?</p>
            <p>As part of offering and providing customizable and personalized services, the PREMIVAL Website career website may use cookies to store and sometimes track information about you. A cookie is a small amount of data that is sent to your browser from a web server and stored on your computer's hard drive. Several features of the PREMIVAL Website recruiting website require that you accept cookies in order to work properly. (See "What choices are available to you regarding collection, use, and distribution of your information" for more information on cookies.)</p>
            <h3>Generally, we use cookies for the following purposes:</h3>
            <p
              class="list"
            >(1) To identify and label all "new" jobs since your last visit to the site.</p>
            <p
              class="list"
            >(2) Optionally to permanently save your username and password on your computer so you don't have to re-enter it each time you visit our site.</p>
